<br>
Hunting EK for spiders is great until too many other people show up to do the same.  A druid with a bear pet was busy wiping out everything the last few times I was there.  With tracking, SoW, and a pet the druid is much better at killing spider than me.<br>
<br>
So, just for something different, I went down to FV.   Using a buffed and DS 54 water pet, I hunted Drachnids.  Not nearly as much silk, but they also drop coin.  My 2 hours gave me over 100pp and a stack of silk swatches.  Pet can easily solo 2 or 3 spiders at a time.  I rarely nuked, just used mana to keep pet buffed.<br>
<br>
No competion, no running around all over EK trying to beat somebody to a spider.  More drachnids than I could wipe out really, they spawn quickly.  And I know druids won't bother to hunt here because it is too hard on their mana <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I also found 2 of the items used in the enchanter spell quest for Illusion: Iksar while hunting.  Finished the quest easily since the other 2 items drop in Lake of Ill Omen and get turned in at FV.<br>
